# Building a Cloud Architecture Diagram

Notes taken from Linkedin Learning 

You can use graphs, charts and ven digrams to present information more efficectively.

You can use prompt engineering:

## Example One

```bash
#Title: IAM Roles and Permissions in AWS, Azure, and GCP diagram structure
-Diagram Structure
    Three overlapping 
        - Each circle represents one cloud provider AWS (left), Azure (right)
## Labels
Font: Clear, sans-serif font (such as Arial or Roboto) for readability
Legend: A small legend explaning key terms

## Content

[AWS(Left Circle)
Azure (Right Circle)
GCP (Bottom Circle)]

[AWS and Azure Overlap
AWS and GCP Overlap
Azure and GCP Overlap
Central Overlap (AWS, Azure, GCP)]
```

## Example Two

```bash

# Title: IAM Roles and Permissions in AWS, Azure, and GCP

## Diagram Structure:
    - **Three overlapping circles** forming a classic venn digram
    - Each circle represents one cloud provider: **AWS** (left), **Azure** (right), **GCP** (bottom)

## Labels
```

